@node pageIntr "Introduction"

  This is the first finished program of many I have in mind. I have been
  composing for some time now. I use an expanded Amiga 1200, with Clari-
  ty 16, and a YAMAHA SY85 synthesiser.

  One  day I realised how user-unfriendly it was to edit voices, perfor-
  mances, and  all the  other stuff in my synth. That´s why I decided to
  build  my own  software to  control the  synth. As I said, this is the
  first  program of a  big idea I  have in  mind: an integrated software
  that  controls  absolutely the  synth. Able to  sequence, edit voices,
  performances and  multi  setup, listen to 16 bit samples and send them
  to the synth, and  other cool stuff, as rhythm  editor, MIDI on-screen
  graphic effect generator, music-thinkers...

  @{b}What does it do ?@{ub} The idea behind  VEd is to  help you  edit VOICEs in
  a SY85  synthesiser. The big difference  between doing it on the synth
  and doing it with VEd, is that in the synth you have  dozens  of menus
  and submenus, and you don´t see much data at the same time, while with
  VEd, you see the data all in ONE screen and modifiable with the mouse.
@endnode
