@node pageHowD
@title "How to use VEd V1.0"

  1. Turn on your synth.
  2. Start Ved from Workbench or Shell.

  Once loaded, the prgram will send  some messages  to get in the  VOICE
  mode, voice INT1 A1. Then, VEd will read and display the data.

  Then you can see the screen divided in 6 horizontal sections:

  1.Name, Waveform, Reverse.
  2.Filter
  3.Pitch
  4.Amplitud
  5.LFO
  6.Effects

  All the data can be modified with the @{"mouse" link pageMous}, except the @{"name" link pageName} of the
  current voice. Some keyboard @{"shortcuts" link pageShor} are also available.
@endnode
@node pageInst
@title "Installing Ved 1.0"

  To install the program just copy VEd and VEdBG in  any  directory, and
  put the @{b}midi.library@{ub} in the 'libs:' directory

  @{b}Requirements:@{ub}
  - Amiga 1200
  - midi.library
  - MIDI interface.
  - Yamaha SY-85 synthesiser.
  
@endnode
@node pageName
@title "How to modify the NAME of a voice"

  Changing the name of the current voice is very  easy : just  type  the
  name  and  press @{b}ENTER@{ub}. The new  name will be  immediatly  sent to the
  synth. You  can use @{b}BACKSPACE@{ub} if you typed the wrong character, or
  press @{b}ESC@{ub} to clear the whole word.
@endnode
@node pageMous
@title "How to operate the mouse"

  There are actually five operations you can do  with  the mouse. Always
  point to the data you would like to change. Then you can :

  @{b}Click with left button.@{ub} This  will  increase  the  variable under the
  pointer in one. If it´s a word, it will get the next possible value:
  SERIAL   -> Lclick -> PARALLEL        ( effect mode )
  101      -> Lclick -> 102             ( any number  )

  @{b}Click with right button.@{ub} This will decrease in one the data.
  PARALLEL -> Rclick -> SERIAL
  102      -> Rclick -> 101

  Data with low value range are cyclic, that is, when they go past their
  maximum value, they will get the minimum value:
  PARALLEL -> Lclick -> OFF -> Lclick -> SERIAL -> Lclick -> PARALLEL

  @{b}Click and Hold with left button.@{ub} Now move  up  or  down. This
  will change the data value up or down, in increments of 1.

  @{b}Click and Hold with right button.@{ub} Same as with  left  button,
  but with increments of 5, for faster operation ( in  some  cases  data
  ranges  from -999  TO 999, and it  would take too long with left mouse
  button ).

  @{b}Click both buttons.@{ub} Reset the variable.

  After releasing the mouse buttons, on any of the cases  above, the new
  data  will be  immediatly  transmited to the  synth. You can  play the
  keyboard to hear how it sounds.

  @{fg fill}Icons/Special variables@{fg text}  
  @{b}Exit icon@{ub}, on the top left corner.
  @{b}Voice selector@{ub}, on the bottom  right  corner. With it, you  can choose
  the  source ( internal  or  card ), the  bank ( 1 - 4 ) and the  voice
  number ( A1 - H7 ). When you choose a  new  voice  to  edit, VEd  will
  automatically read it from the synth. The new data will  be redrawn on
  the screen. @{b}BE CAREFUL@{ub} with selecting CARD source  when  there  is  no
  CARD plugged.
  @{b}Waveform source.@{ub} You can choose  between  internal  waveform  or  user
  waveform clicking just before the waveform numbre, on the P or I. When
  it´s an internal waveform, its name will appear after its number.
  @{b}Fixed/Variable.@{ub} Choose the tone generation  method  clicking over  the
  "Fixed:" or "Note" titles  on the PITCH area, on the  left side of the
  screen
  @{b}Note-variables.@{ub} Those  data  items  that  define a key ( it looks like
  C#+2 ) can be changed holding the left mouse  button on that item, and
  playing a key on the synth.
@endnode
@node pageShor
@title "Shortcuts"

  Besides  the method  explained for typing  the name of  the voice, and
  using the ESC, ENTER and BACKSPACE commands, there are 2 (wow!) opera-
  tive commands:

  @{b}CTRL-q@{ub} : Quit the program

  @{b}CTRL-f@{ub} : Set the CutOff filter frequency. How ? Type a value, like 30, 
  and then hit CTRL-f.

  If someone  finds useful  changing  all  the  data  with @{b}CTRL-key@{ub} type
  of commands, tell me and I will add more key-commands.

@endnode
